<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="751" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/5–1145</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President Truman to the Acting Secretary
                                of State</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">and the Foreign Economic
                                Administrator</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crowley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-11">May 11,
                                1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I approve the policy of lend-lease supplies to the U.S.S.R. recommended
                            in your memorandum of May 11, 1945. In carrying out the policy, you
                            should, until further notice, proceed on the assumption that the
                            U.S.S.R. will enter into the war against Japan.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>